I cried. However, I understand why it had to be you.
You were so worried that your legacy would be your failure, that you would...
body:
I cried. However, I understand why it had to be you.

You were so worried that your legacy would be your failure, that you would not be able to save your loved ones.. My hero, you made it. You got what you wanted.

Robert Downey Jr, oh man, actually you were the hero all along. Being able to bring Tony Stark to life like that, you are something special!

Endgame was somewhat bittersweet, thank you Avengers for everything..

Iron man, you will be remembered ♡

summary: Okay you know what? I think we’ve lost site of how GOT 8x03 NEEDS to turn out.
title: Okay you know what? I think we’ve lost site of how GOT 8x03 NEEDS to turn out.
body:
The Battle of Winterfell is interrupted by a sudden flash of white light. Suddenly, there stands a dark-haired man in red armor the likes of which no one has ever seen before. He looks around, bewildered. His eyes fall on the soldiers, then on the White Walkers and their Night King. He looks the blue-eyed ghoul up and down. Then he mutters “You have got to be kidding me,” and he shoots fire from his arms.

BOOM.

The army of the dead falls that night, and before long, a rumor is spreading across Westeros like wildfire: there is a long-lost Stark in Winterfell.

Tony, meanwhile, is not enjoying what he calls his “Wizard of Oz meets Lord of the Rings trip.”

summary: Marvel (Iron Man) Drabble
title: Marvel (Iron Man) Drabble
body:
pairing - reader x iron man (platonic)

warnings - death, angst, ENDGAME SPOILERS, minor language

word count - IDK

setting - Reader was Stark’s best friend and colleague. Following his death, they are left with a chip with his life’s work on it.

A/N - Here are the extra feels no one asked for.

Please send me your requests, I am in dire need of prompts.

________________________________________________

Flick

Pepper let the wreath float away, tears dripping down her face for the man she loved.

Flick

One by one, the Avengers paid their respects and left to go inside. Each took their turn reminding Morgan that her father had been a great man and that there would never be another like him. Never.

Flick

You stood alone on the porch, watching as the tiny memorial floated away. Such a small tribute for someone who had saved half the universe. Yet it was the only way anyone knew to honour a man who had everything.

Flick

The evening was warm, yet carried with it an inexplicable chill. The sun waved goodbye through the trees as Y/H/C hair was blown with each breath of wind, your own breath calm and deep. The only way you knew how to handle these emotions was control. Just like Stark.

Flick

The chip was flung from it’s case, before you pushed it back in again.

Flick

And again. On that tiny piece of slate coloured metal was a life’s work. Two lives work. The two of you had met shortly after 2008 after you came to work at Stark Industries. You were by no means the smartest person in the room, yet you saw the world at an angle which couldn’t help but intrigue the billionaire.

Flick

Your ideas collided with his, forming technology previously undreamt of. Late nights of work and early mornings of drinking and good-spirited banter made up your friendship, with your seemingly uncompadible personalities expanding the tech empire above and beyond. Even Banner watched on in amazement as you went about micro-wiring each of the nano tech molecules as Stark connected his arc reactor to the sheet of smooth, cloth-like metal. The two of you were unstoppable, limited only by the speed at which your machines would work.

Flick

Here it was. Maybe you’d give it to Morgan one day, when she could understand. Maybe Pepper could hold onto it until then. You paused, thumb grazing the Stark Industries logo. Flipping it over, you read the back for the nth time.

                                             You bloody bastard.

                                                                Thanks,

                                                                     Stark

A grin lit up your tired features. You knew what he would have wanted.

Kissing the metal, you rolled it over in your palm and threw the chip as far as you could into the water.

Plop

Morgan would work it out herself. You were going to teach her until she became just like her father. No, better than him. That’s the Stark legacy, after all.

Following was never their style.
